ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The class was a good overview of basic principles in catalysis, and how people can conduct scientific research based on catalysis. I would recommend it probably to any chemical engineer, and any student interested in the subject.
Can at least audit it. It is useful.
Highly recommended for people working in this field.Recommended as an overview course for other ChemE students.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course has broadened my knowledge but doesn't directly contribute to my perspective dissertation.
It extended my knowledge of catalysts and the means in which they are tested
